</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"3b503b84636b"><strong>Runbook alignment</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"abed905f90b6">
<li local-id=3D"c2a53295b8a1">
<p local-id=3D"f14c2c3fc8f4">A published SD-facing batch failure process ex=
ists (<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://manulife.service-now.com/k=
b_knowledge.do?sysparm_query=3Dnumber=3DKB0033382" rel=3D"nofollow"><strong=
>KB0033382</strong></a><strong>: Global Batch Job Failure =E2=80=93 SD Proc=
ess</strong>), but it is oriented to <strong>batch failures</strong>, not <=
strong>=E2=80=9Cbatch succeeded but produced wrong outbound communications.=
=E2=80=9D</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c39bf18e9dc9">
<p local-id=3D"a4685da78d39">This incident needs a dedicated <strong>=E2=80=
=9COutbound Messaging Mis-send / Mass Notification=E2=80=9D</strong> runboo=
k (containment + suppression + validation).</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"6fda50cdb674"><strong>L1/L2 recovery feasibility</strong></p=
>
<ul local-id=3D"cf97d05995e2">
<li local-id=3D"42d87c839b7b">
<p local-id=3D"bd85ef7f97a7">With the right controls, L1/L2 can execute: <s=
trong>pause outbound sends</strong>, <strong>activate suppression</strong>,=
 <strong>notify stakeholders</strong>, <strong>confirm message volume retur=
ns to baseline</strong>=E2=80=94but those controls must exist and be safe.<=
/p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"3fc423c3e74f">
<h3 local-id=3D"76037120fa59" id=3D"IncidentAnalysis:UnintendedSMS/LINEMess=
agesSentto70,000CustomersDuetoDataUpdateError-MTTV(Validation)">MTTV (Valid=
ation)</h3>
<p local-id=3D"2b37bfdb83f4"><strong>Validation approach (table)</strong></=
